result.execSummary:
The defendant Tina M. Klemp was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Tina M. Klemp in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls @ 1:45 pm.  Plea advisement filed. State gives plea agreement, plea to ct's 2 & 3, ct 1 dismissed & read, withheld sentence 2 years probation, counseling as needed, costs. State has tried to comply with victim rights, however, notice came back, Parties agree to plea agreement,  Ct 2 Battery, Domestic, no contest plea, Ct 3 D.C., Domestic, no contest plea, Ct 1 Dismissed consistent to plea agreement, Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights.  Atty Nocco finds factual basis & is satisfied.  Court finds plea are freely & voluntarily given, accepts plea & finds def. Guilty to Battery, in ct 2 & D.C. in ct 3.  Def. has nothing to say.  Court accepts plea agreement & orders in ct 2 withheld sentence 2 years probation, counseling deemed appropriate by agent & costs & 200 DNA surcharge. ct 3 withheld sentence 2 years probation, concurrent to ct 2 Counseling & costs & $200 DNA surcharge. Bond applied to costs.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Restitution to be held open for 60 days. Atty Nocco may request hearing if objects. Def. advised of postconviction rights.

Defendant Tina M. Klemp not in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State request that the no contact provision be lifted.  Court will lift no contact with C. H.  Copy of minutes to Sheriff dept.

Defendant Tina M. Klemp in court with attorney Jessica L. Schuster.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Special appearance by Atty Schuster.  Time limits waived for preliminary.  Complaint received. Bond will contine with condition  Status conference scheduled for August 25, 2014 at 03:30 pm.
